{
  "text": "In the ongoing SEAT project, the ambition over the coming years is to describe four major aquaculture exports farmed in Asia. Detailed LCAs will be conducted of a representative sample of each major farming system, supported by a larger scoping survey collecting basic data for 1,600 grow-out farmers in the region. Foreground data will also be collected on other actors in the value chain, including feed producers, processing plants, hatcheries, nurseries, and fishmeal factories in each country. The results of this research are to be presented in inventory and impact assessment reports over the upcoming years, with the ambition to adopt the recommendations suggested above. These efforts together with several other LCA studies published after this review (e.g., [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] will hopefully improve our current knowledge of the impacts of the aquaculture sector and promote best practice.",
